oject?</li>\n</ul><br><strong>Assessment</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Consistent and enthusiastic involvement in all phases of the lesson, including brainstorming, collaborative art creation, group sharing, and discussions.</li>\n<li>Comprehension of Global Goal 16 themes (e.g., peace, justice, community) as demonstrated through the symbolism in the collaborative art and verbal explanations.</li>\n<li>Originality and effectiveness in applying the “exquisite corpse” method, embracing its collaborative nature, the element of chance, and the unexpected juxtaposition of individual contributions.</li>\n<li>How clearly and powerfully the finished collaborative artwork communicates its intended message. Did the piece successfully provoke thought or emotion related to peace and justice?</li>\n<li>Ability to work effectively within the small groups, contributing ideas, respecting diverse artistic choices, and collaborating cohesively to create the shared piece.</li>\n<li>Nuance and depth of understanding demonstrated in reflections, particularly concerning the role of documentary theater in advocating for social justice and the complexities of achieving peace and fairness.</li>\n</ul>"} {sdgColor} />

